.TH "iio_dma_buffer_read" 9 "iio_dma_buffer_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iio_dma_buffer_read \- DMA buffer read callback
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" iio_dma_buffer_read
.BI "(struct iio_buffer *buffer "  ","
.BI "size_t n "  ","
.BI "char __user *user_buffer "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buffer" 12
Buffer to read form
.IP "n" 12
Number of bytes to read
.IP "user_buffer" 12
Userspace buffer to copy the data to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Should be used as the read callback for iio_buffer_access_ops
struct for DMA buffers.
